snippet.textDisplay:
This was our last video for the year 12019 of the Human Era. And what a year it was. So much stuff happened everywhere. To so many different people.
Calendars and holidays are just imaginary but they help us to cut our lives into pieces that our brains can handle.
We are leaving 12019 behind with a weird mixture of disillusion and hope. The world is screwed up. But we can fix it. In a few days this year will be over. And we all get to try again.
Thank you for watching our videos and for sticking around for so many years. See you all in 12020.

Hello.
Can you make an video about great filter in 2020, specifically "robot evolution" (is that word correct, im bad in english?)

I think this is a great filter because: (for short, skip to the third)
1. We need energy to exist (through food, oxygen) and response our needs (example: hold your smartphone to watch this beautiful and useful scientific video)
We need so much energy to survive (and loss energy at work, by war, etc.)
And the energy we need is increasing, but most of us dont have enough of that (not mention energy trade among nations yet)

2. We have three solution:
- First, gather more with science (we need more and more energy to do it because it is harder and harder to find a way)
And gather more = more pollution (from the way we get it)
- Second, decrease energy loss (stop war, saving food and things, bla x3.14...)
But the one we save is less than the one we need, and ask the both side: "do you want to stop the war?" (Ok that is so complicated)

- Third and especially: Evolution ,
from human to robots (suppose that we can do it)

So this is a great evolution or our extinction ?
And another important issues: If we choose that way, when and how will we do it?
